[Amit Varma]: demonetization like first of all there were no benefits as i wrote repeatedly at the time but

01:50:19.520 --> 01:50:25.120
[Amit Varma]: even had there been great benefits the costs are being borne by someone else and that's not uh sort

01:50:25.120 --> 01:50:32.720
[Amit Varma]: of morally acceptable and on this same sort of strand you know earlier you had spoken about how

01:50:32.720 --> 01:50:37.200
[Amit Varma]: in a different context in the context of language about how as a journalist say you go to a village

01:50:37.200 --> 01:50:40.400
[Amit Varma]: you meet the sarpanch you're talking to the sarpanch but you don't know enough of the

01:50:40.400 --> 01:50:45.760
[Amit Varma]: language of the marginalized people there to be able to converse with them so the sarpanch becomes

01:50:45.760 --> 01:50:53.200
[Amit Varma]: a sort of a mediator through which uh you access all of that this seems similar to me to uh you

01:50:53.200 --> 01:50:59.120
[Amit Varma]: know how the british developed their notion of what hinduism is i had a great episode with manu

01:50:59.120 --> 01:51:06.080
[Amit Varma]: pillay on this uh uh where uh and he's written at length but you know and so have so many others

01:51:06.080 --> 01:51:10.880
[Amit Varma]: where the british come here they're only interlocutors are you know the sarpanches

01:51:10.880 --> 01:51:16.880
[Amit Varma]: of the time as it were which are the upper caste brahmans who sell them this particular uh notion

01:51:16.880 --> 01:51:21.920
[Amit Varma]: of what hinduism is with the varna system and the castes and all of that a very manusmriti notion

01:51:21.920 --> 01:51:26.400
[Amit Varma]: and they extrapolate that and that becomes part of their notion and that's how they govern

01:51:26.400 --> 01:51:32.880
[Amit Varma]: and suddenly all of these diverse identities and traditions and customs are subsumed in this larger

01:51:32.880 --> 01:51:38.320
[Amit Varma]: narrative that develops over time into this monolithic uh brahmanical thing which is which

01:51:38.320 --> 01:51:44.000
[Amit Varma]: is not really so great and and which is not really so dominant rather and it seems to me that that's

01:51:44.000 --> 01:51:50.320
[Amit Varma]: also you know you've you quoted uh tony joseph uh in your book tony was um on my show as well

01:51:50.320 --> 01:51:57.280
[Amit Varma]: and the big revelation of his book is that what we know now from genetic evidence is that we were an

01:51:57.280 --> 01:52:05.680
[Amit Varma]: inclusive society till about the year uh zero or you know till sort of the start of uh till 180 so

01:52:05.680 --> 01:52:10.960
[Amit Varma]: to say and then one gangetic plain strand of thought about what hinduism wins over and you

01:52:10.960 --> 01:52:17.760
[Amit Varma]: have endogamy and which is why uh you know david reich refers to the indian subcontinent as not a

01:52:17.760 --> 01:52:23.040
[Amit Varma]: large population like the han chinese would be but as a collection of many small populations

